<taxonomicName id="4C104D2BFFBD9A60FE35F9F07E3AF9EE" authorityName="Merr. A. Habit" authorityYear="1925" box="[457,610,1601,1627]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvilimba">
<emphasis id="B964EABAFFBD9A60FE35F9F07E3AF9EE" box="[457,610,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">B. parvilimba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<emphasis id="B964EABAFFBD9A60FCCEF9F07F84F9EE" box="[818,988,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">B. mindanensis</emphasis>
but significantly differs in having smaller leaves and capsules.
</paragraph>
