<taxonomicName id="4C104D2BFFBD9A60FDAEF9417F6DF8B9" authorityName="Merr. A. Habit" authorityYear="1925" box="[594,821,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvilimba">
<emphasis id="B964EABAFFBD9A60FDAEF9417F6DF8B9" box="[594,821,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Begonia parvilimba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="3B783CF5FFBD9A60FCC3F9407E1BF8C2" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3699170305" collectionCode="L" location="Ekam River" municipality="Malangas. The area" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Zamboanga">
is currently known from two localities in 
<collectingRegion id="49D4F84AFFBD9A60FADBF94079F3F8B9" box="[1319,1451,1778,1804]" country="Philippines" name="Zamboanga" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Zamboanga</collectingRegion>
Peninsula. The 
<typeStatus id="54AB880AFFBD9A60FEC9F8A47D3DF885" box="[309,357,1814,1840]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">type</typeStatus>
locality is now part of the populated, site of coal mining municipality of 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BCBACD2FFBD9A60FB6BF8A4792BF885" box="[1175,1395,1814,1840]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Malangas. The area</collectingMunicipality>
with the recently found record for the species at the 
<location id="8ECF6073FFBD9A60FD67F88B7F7AF8E6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B987BEFFBD9A60FF74FDD97E1BF79C:8ECF6073FFBD9A60FD67F88B7F7AF8E6" box="[667,802,1849,1875]" municipality="Malangas. The area" name="Ekam River" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" stateProvince="Zamboanga">Ekam River</location>
is an inhabited, previously kaingin area and now covered with invasive species 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D2BFFBD9A60FE87F8EF7E7FF8C2" box="[379,551,1885,1911]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" genus="Piper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aduncum">
<emphasis id="B964EABAFFBD9A60FE87F8EF7E7FF8C2" box="[379,551,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Piper aduncum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectionCode id="ED01AE6DFFBD9A60FDD1F8EF7E1BF8C2" box="[557,579,1885,1911]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
., 
<materialsCitation id="3B783CF5FFBD9A60FDAEF8EF7E79F79C" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3699170303" collectionCode="CR" county="Ekam" location="After" municipality="Here" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Zamboanga">
in addition the nearby 
<collectingCounty id="62CE4E24FFBD9A60FCB0F8EF7FD5F8C2" box="[844,909,1885,1911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Ekam</collectingCounty>
waterfalls is frequently visited by tourists. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BCBACD2FFBD9A60FA92F8EF79FFF8C2" box="[1390,1447,1885,1911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="168">Here</collectingMunicipality>
, only one population with two individuals were observed. 
<location id="8ECF6073FFBD9A60FCE8F8327F17F82F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B987BEFFBD9A60FF74FDD97E1BF79C:8ECF6073FFBD9A60FCE8F8327F17F82F" box="[788,847,1920,1946]" county="Ekam" municipality="Here" name="After" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" stateProvince="Zamboanga">After</location>
16 months of fieldwork with 5 or 6 times/month site visits, no additional populations nor individuals were found. 
<location id="8ECF6073FFBD9A60FCC2F8167FF9F80B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B987BEFFBD9A60FF74FDD97E1BF79C:8ECF6073FFBD9A60FCC2F8167FF9F80B" box="[830,929,1956,1982]" county="Ekam" municipality="Here" name="The area" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" stateProvince="Zamboanga">The area</location>
is not currently protected under the country’s 
<location id="8ECF6073FFBD9A60FF74F8757E26F854" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B987BEFFBD9A60FF74FDD97E1BF79C:8ECF6073FFBD9A60FF74F8757E26F854" box="[136,638,1991,2017]" county="Ekam" municipality="Here" name="National Integrated Protected Areas System" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" stateProvince="Zamboanga">National Integrated Protected Areas System</location>
by the 
<location id="8ECF6073FFBD9A60FD26F87A7844F854" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B987BEFFBD9A60FF74FDD97E1BF79C:8ECF6073FFBD9A60FD26F87A7844F854" box="[730,1052,1991,2018]" county="Ekam" municipality="Here" name="Department of Environment" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" stateProvince="Zamboanga">Department of Environment</location>
and Natural Resources. Given the ongoing habitat change and the small number of &lt;50 mature individuals, it is prudent to provisionally assess this species as 
<location id="8ECF6073FFBD9A60FF02F7BC7DADF79D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B987BEFFBD9A60FF74FDD97E1BF79C:8ECF6073FFBD9A60FF02F7BC7DADF79D" box="[254,501,2062,2088]" county="Ekam" municipality="Here" name="Critically Endangered" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" stateProvince="Zamboanga">Critically Endangered</location>
<collectionCode id="ED01AE6DFFBD9A60FE00F7BD7E79F79C" box="[508,545,2063,2089]" country="Costa Rica" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15652" name="Museo Nacional de Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="168" type="Herbarium">CR</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
D.
</paragraph>
